{
  "texts": [
    "For those studies that contained two types of manipulations, we coded 0.5 for each category.",
    "As described in the main body, most framing experiments study heterogeneous treatment effects across population subgroups.",
    "We thus conducted a critical appraisal to test the robustness and substantial relevance of reported heterogeneous framing effects by re-analyzing ten typical and widely cited studies that reported heterogeneous framing effects across partisanship subgroups and made replication material publicly available.",
    "These re-analyses are not representative of all published framing experiments.",
    "Unfortunately, however, the quantity of publicly available data material is very limited, so we could not fully assess existing results' robustness."
  ]
}